{{- /*
DH project secrets bundle for ~/.config/dh/secrets.env, consumed by
D:/dh/mise.toml via `_.file = "~/.config/dh/secrets.env"`. mise reads
this once per shell load — solving the original "auth on every cd"
problem (mise's exec() was re-running op/cat on every directory change).

Resolved once via batched `op inject` in .chezmoi.toml.tmpl, then reused
from `.secrets.*` here.

Refresh after rotating any of these in 1Password:
    chezmoi apply --init

`private_` prefix → 0600 on Unix; no-op on Windows ACLs.

Add more dh-project-scoped env vars below as you need them. Keep them
narrow: only secrets you want available whenever you `cd D:\dh\*`.
*/ -}}
DH_GITLAB_TOKEN={{ .secrets.dh_gitlab_pat }}
